# =============================================================================
# Commit everything under ~/.claude/skills EXCEPT secrets and generated junk.
# (Switched from the earlier opt-in whitelist — all skills are now tracked.)
# =============================================================================

# --- Secrets — NEVER commit ---------------------------------------------------
# .env holds Tavily/Exa keys + X auth_token. .env.* covers .env.local etc.
# .env.example is the committed template (re-included below).
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Local, machine-specific Claude permission allowlists — not shared.
**/settings.local.json

# --- Generated / runtime junk -------------------------------------------------
# Runtime caches (docs cache, browser profiles, etc.)
**/.cache/

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# Node
node_modules/

# Generated per-run artifacts
results.html

# automate-browser scratch output (screenshots, scraped pages, etc.)
automate-browser/tmp/

# --- Symlinked third-party skills (not ours to commit) -----------------------
# Skills installed by other apps (Conan, etc.) sometimes drop a symlink into
# ~/.claude/skills. Their source lives elsewhere; just ignore the symlink here.
/conan-change-radio

# --- External skill installer (shadcn/ui official skill, etc.) ---------------
# Compose with external skills; don't vendor their source. `skills-lock.json`
# (committed) pins the version + hash so a fresh checkout can re-install
# deterministically. The install artifacts live here and stay local:
/.agents/
/.claude/skills/
# Plus top-level symlinks we add by hand so each skill is discoverable as a
# *user-global* skill (the installer drops them under .claude/skills/ which
# only works when cwd is here; the symlinks at top-level resolve the same
# install from any project). Same pattern as /conan-change-radio above.
/shadcn
/next-best-practices
/design-md

# --- Session handoff (per-machine; rebuilt each session via /handoff) --------
# HANDOFF.md is the resume-ready session-state file the handoff skill writes;
# .claude/current-task.txt is the one-line label the status line reads;
# .claude/handoff-archive/ is the PreCompact hook's rolling snapshot history
# (machine-local debug history, not curated memory — that lives in
# ~/.claude/projects/<encoded>/memory/ via the typed-memory system).
# All session-local and don't belong in the shared repo.
/HANDOFF.md
/.claude/current-task.txt
/.claude/handoff-archive/

# macOS
.DS_Store
